Document: BaseButton
Path: godot/classes/class_basebutton.rst
Summary: This section describes the properties available for configuring a BaseButton, including its action mode, group, input mask, pressed state, disabled state, shortcut behavior, and toggle mode.

Property Descriptions

action_mode (ActionMode): Determines when the button is considered clicked. Default: 1.
Method: set_action_mode(value: ActionMode)
Method: get_action_mode()

button_group (ButtonGroup): The ButtonGroup associated with the button. Not to be confused with node groups. Note: The button will be configured as a radio button if a ButtonGroup is assigned to it.
Method: set_button_group(value: ButtonGroup)
Method: get_button_group()

button_mask (bitfield[MouseButtonMask]): Binary mask to choose which mouse buttons this button will respond to. To allow both left-click and right-click, use MOUSE_BUTTON_MASK_LEFT | MOUSE_BUTTON_MASK_RIGHT. Default: 1.
Method: set_button_mask(value: bitfield[MouseButtonMask])
Method: get_button_mask()

button_pressed (bool): If true, the button's state is pressed. Means the button is pressed down or toggled (if toggle_mode is active). Only works if toggle_mode is true. Note: Changing the value of button_pressed will result in toggled to be emitted. If you want to change the pressed state without emitting that signal, use set_pressed_no_signal(). Default: false.
Method: set_pressed(value: bool)
Method: is_pressed()

disabled (bool): If true, the button is in disabled state and can't be clicked or toggled. Note: If the button is disabled while held down, button_up will be emitted. Default: false.
Method: set_disabled(value: bool)
Method: is_disabled()

keep_pressed_outside (bool): If true, the button stays pressed when moving the cursor outside the button while pressing it. Note: This property only affects the button's visual appearance. Signals will be emitted at the same moment regardless of this property's value. Default: false.
Method: set_keep_pressed_outside(value: bool)
Method: is_keep_pressed_outside()

shortcut (Shortcut): Shortcut associated to the button.
Method: set_shortcut(value: Shortcut)
Method: get_shortcut()

shortcut_feedback (bool): If true, the button will highlight for a short amount of time when its shortcut is activated. If false and toggle_mode is false, the shortcut will activate without any visual feedback. Default: true.
Method: set_shortcut_feedback(value: bool)
Method: is_shortcut_feedback()

shortcut_in_tooltip (bool): If true, the button will add information about its shortcut in the tooltip. This includes the shortcut's events and its Resource.resource_name. If both events and name are empty, the shortcut will not be included. Note: This property does nothing when the tooltip control is customized using Control._make_custom_tooltip(). Default: true.
Method: set_shortcut_in_tooltip(value: bool)
Method: is_shortcut_in_tooltip_enabled()

toggle_mode (bool): If true, the button is in toggle mode. Makes the button flip state between pressed and unpressed each time its area is clicked. Default: false.
Method: set_toggle_mode(value: bool)
Method: is_toggle_mode()
---CHUNK---
Document: BaseButton
Path: godot/classes/class_basebutton.rst
Summary: This section describes several virtual and public methods of the BaseButton class, including those for handling press and toggle events, retrieving draw mode, checking hover state, and setting the pressed state without emitting signals.

Method: _pressed() → void
Called when the button is pressed. If you need to know the button's pressed state (and toggle_mode is active), use _toggled() instead.

Method: _toggled(toggled_on: bool) → void
Called when the button is toggled (only if toggle_mode is active).

Method: get_draw_mode() → DrawMode
Returns the visual state used to draw the button. This is useful mainly when implementing your own draw code by either overriding _draw() or connecting to "draw" signal. The visual state of the button is defined by the DrawMode enum.

Method: is_hovered() → bool
Returns true if the mouse has entered the button and has not left it yet.

Method: set_pressed_no_signal(pressed: bool) → void
Changes the button_pressed state of the button, without emitting toggled. Use when you just want to change the state of the button without sending the pressed event (e.g. when initializing scene). Only works if toggle_mode is true.
Note: This method doesn't unpress other buttons in button_group.